# Brand asset governance

The directory `Logo/` at the workspace root is the authoritative source for all Sunnah Remedies branding. The `public/brand/` directory contains the deployed copies of those assets.

## Rules

- Read the Brand Guidelines before modifying branding.
- Prefer SVG assets over PNG unless a raster format is specifically required (e.g. favicon fallbacks, Apple Touch Icon).
- Use only official logo variations from the Brand Package.
- Never redraw or recreate the logo.
- Never distort proportions.
- Never recolour assets.
- Never apply effects, shadows, gradients, or glows.
- Never introduce unofficial branding.
- Never substitute another wordmark.
- Never use placeholder logos.
- Import logos through the central Brand configuration at `src/lib/brand.ts`.
- Keep branding consistent across the entire application.

## Central configuration

All brand asset paths are defined in `src/lib/brand.ts`. Components must import from this file rather than referencing `/brand/` paths directly. To change branding, replace the source files in `Logo/` and `public/brand/` — never edit code to alter the visual identity.

## Colour reference

| Token        | Hex       |
|-------------|-----------|
| Deep Emerald | `#0E3B2E` |
| Antique Gold | `#C7A25A` |
| Warm Ivory   | `#F6F3EE` |

## Typography

- **Libre Baskerville** — wordmark, headings (converted to outlines in SVGs)
- **Inter** — descriptor line, body, labels

The Brand Package overrides all previous branding implementations.
